A young pilot and his father had a lucky escape when they were forced to crash land in a wheat field in East Yorkshire.

The 18-year-old man encountered low-lying cloud after taking off from Beverly Airfield and made a ‘precautionary landing’ in the wheat.

The pilot, who had recently qualified, and his father, both jumped out of the Cessna A150 unharmed after the landing.

