A local resident who was first on the scene said: ‘We came round the corner and we rushed into the field.

‘Already the pilot was out and on the phone and he gave us a thumbs up to say he was OK.’

The Cessna A150 was forced to make the ‘precautionary landing’ as low-lying cloud closed in near Keyingham, East Yorkshire.

Peter
 Spencer, company secretary of Hull Aero Club Ltd, where the aircraft is
 based, said: ‘The pilot had elected to do a precautionary landing after
 encountering adverse weather conditions.

'During the landing the 
nosewheel caught on the uneven field, tipping the aircraft forwards.

