‘He
 did what he considered appropriate and the testimony of that was that 
they both walked away. He took a considered judgement to prevent a 
further predicament.

‘Both 
the pilot and his father were wearing harnesses and were uninjured. The 
aeroplane lost its nose wheel, but is repairable.’

Mr Spencer said the club has an ‘enviable’ safety record with few incidents during its 85-year history.

Both the Air Accident Investigation Branch and the Civil Aviation Authority have been informed.

